.TH "phylink_of_phy_connect" 9 "phylink_of_phy_connect" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
phylink_of_phy_connect \- connect the PHY specified in the DT mode.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" phylink_of_phy_connect
.BI "(struct phylink *pl "  ","
.BI "struct device_node *dn "  ","
.BI "u32 flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pl" 12
a pointer to a \fIstruct phylink\fP returned from \fBphylink_create\fP
.IP "dn" 12
a pointer to a \fIstruct device_node\fP.
.IP "flags" 12
PHY-specific flags to communicate to the PHY device driver
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Connect the phy specified in the device node \fIdn\fP to the phylink instance
specified by \fIpl\fP. Actions specified in \fBphylink_connect_phy\fP will be
performed.

Returns 0 on success or a negative errno.
